\pard\plain \sa180\sb180\ltrch\loch {The frantic pace lasted for two blocks, his footsteps echoing in the narrow alleyways between the old faculty halls. Only when he was sure he was out of immediate sight did his sprint slow to a brisk, panting walk. The high-stakes tension of the council room began to dissipate, replaced by the quiet hum of the Edenfield night. The only sounds were the cold wind whistling through the eaves of the buildings and the rhythmic chirp of crickets and cicadas hidden in the manicured campus shrubbery.}
\par\plain {He ducked behind the thick trunk of an oak tree near the edge of the quad, his heart still hammering against his ribs. He pulled out his smartphone, the screen lighting up his face in the gloom. The first thing he checked was his call log. One missed call. From Madeleine. His stomach tightened again.}
\par\plain {He swiped over to his photo gallery. The pictures were hasty, some blurry, but he\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92d gotten what he needed. He scrolled past photos of mundane university correspondence, budget sheets, and then, he found it. A clear shot of a personnel transfer document. His finger zoomed in on a specific line.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 Previous Occupation: Military Alchemist.}{ }{\f0\fs24\i1 Last Held Post: Instructor, Crownstead Military Academy.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Interesting\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 Eddie whispered to himself, a grim satisfaction cutting through his anxiety. He wasn't just guessing anymore. He had proof.}
\par\plain {It was then that his phone buzzed violently in his hand, the screen lighting up with her name again. He accepted it instantly.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hey, Madeleine, I think I found a lead to\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {There was a sharp breath of relief on the other end. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Eddie? Eddie? Hello? It\u8217\'92s me.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Madeleine?\u8221\'94 His back straightened against the tree bark. \u8220\'93Are you\u8230\'85 okay? You sound\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Listen,\u8221\'94 she cut in, voice taut and quick, like a pulled string. \u8220\'93I don\u8217\'92t have time to explain. I need you tonight to discuss something.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Eddie blinked, confused by her tone. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Wait, what\u8217\'92s happened? What\u8217\'92s going on?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94 Her voice cut out for a second, dissolving into a faint crackle. \u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s Professor Hudson. I think he knows\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 Bzzzt.}
\par\plain {A loud burst of static screamed through the speaker. Eddie yanked the phone away from his ear, flinching.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Madeleine?\u8221\'94 he called into the noise, his thumb hovering over the redial button. \u8220\'93Hello? Madeleine?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Silence. Then a low mechanical whir. Then nothing. He glanced back in the direction of the faculty building and his blood ran cold. Two familiar, bulky silhouettes had emerged onto the lawn, moving under the lamplight, already searching. The Student Council members were free.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Come on\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 he muttered, pressing the phone harder to his ear.}
\par\plain {Suddenly\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0  }{\f0\fs24\i1 Click.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hello?\u8221\'94 he tried again, his breath held.}
\par\plain {A gasp on the other end. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93E-Eddie!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {He gripped the phone tighter. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Madeleine, what\u8217\'92s happening?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I think someone\u8217\'92s following me.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {His stomach dropped. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Where are you?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {There was a pause. A rustle of fabric. Then, distantly through the speaker, he heard the creak of a booth door opening. Her voice dropped to a terrified whisper.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92m at my apartment. Just past the old fence. Near the east ward sign. There\u8217\'92s someone\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 he\u8217\'92s not moving, but\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {The line cracked again, loud and sharp.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I\u8217\'92ve got my wand\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 he\u8217\'92s coming closer\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Eddie, I\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 \u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 Pop.}
\par\plain {The line went dead.}
\par\plain {Eddie stood there, frozen, the soft dial tone humming against his ear like a dirge. The phone felt like a block of ice in his hand.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 Someone\loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8217\'92s following me... he\u8217\'92s coming closer...}
\par\plain {He looked up from his phone, his eyes darting into the darkness of the campus. The two bulky silhouettes of the Student Council members were still there, fanning out across the lawn, but they felt distant now, like a problem from another lifetime. Expulsion. Dorm confinement. None of it mattered. The methodical, institutional threat of Victoria Aynesworth was nothing compared to the raw, immediate terror in Madeleine\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s voice.}
\par\plain {His mind raced, replaying her words. }{\f0\fs24\i1 My apartment... past the old fence... near the east ward sign.}{ The east ward. That was back the way he came. Back towards them.}
\par\plain {He didn't hesitate.}
\par\plain {Panic, worry, and a white-hot surge of determination erased every instinct for self-preservation. He shoved his phone into his pocket and broke from the cover of the trees, sprinting back onto the main path. He wasn't running from danger anymore. He was running towards his friend.}
\par\plain {He saw them under the next gaslamp\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 Victoria pointing, directing her two guards. They saw him at the same moment. A look of triumph flashed across Victoria\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s face. Their quarry was cornered.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Get him!\u8221\'94 she bellowed, her voice echoing across the silent quad.}
\par\plain {The two guards moved to intercept, forming a wall of muscle to block his path. But Eddie didn't slow down. He didn't try to change direction. He ran straight at them.}
\par\plain {Just as the first guard reached for him, Eddie feinted left and then cut hard to the right, ducking under a clumsy, outstretched arm. He dodged past the second guard with a burst of desperate speed, his feet pounding on the stone path. He ran right past them, leaving them standing there, bewildered.}
\par\plain {Even Victoria was stunned into silence for a moment, her mouth slightly agape. What the hell was this kid thinking? He had a clear path to escape, and yet he was running deeper into campus, straight through them.}
\par\plain {Her shock lasted only a second before it hardened back into fury.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Get him! Don\u8217\'92t let him escape!\u8221\'94 Victoria shouted, pointing in the direction Eddie was now heading. Recovering, the two guards turned and gave chase, their heavy footfalls thudding behind him as they pursued him into the night.}
