\par\plain {The lecture hall had emptied out ten minutes ago, but Will\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s pace was slow as he walked the stone path back toward the dorms. The sun had long since set, and the Edenfield campus was bathed in the cool, silver light of the moon and the warm, flickering glow of gaslamps. The wind was picking up, rustling through the old oak trees and making the long shadows of the spires dance and twist like living things.}
\par\plain {He clutched the strap of his satchel, his mind miles away from his evening lecture on transmutational theory. It was on Eddie. Always on Eddie these days. He remembered their last conversation in the infirmary, the fight about him getting involved. Now, Eddie was distant, secretive, always buried in some restricted text or slipping away without a word. Will was worried. Worried about the Chimaeras, yes, but more worried about his best friend getting himself expelled. Or worse.}
\par\plain {He was so lost in thought that he didn't hear the light, quick footsteps behind him.}
\par\plain {Suddenly\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 }{\f0\fs24\i1 bam!}
\par\plain {A pair of arms wrapped around his chest from behind, and a familiar weight landed on his back. Will jumped, his heart lurching into his throat as he stumbled forward, nearly dropping his satchel.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hey there, mr. downer!\u8221\'94 Ashley\u8217\'92s cheerful voice chirped right next to his ear. She let go, jogging to walk beside him, a wide grin on her face. Her Witchcraft robes were still draped over her arm. \u8220\'93How\u8217\'92d class go?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Will took a deep breath, trying to slow his racing pulse. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Ash, don\u8217\'92t do that,\u8221\'94 he said, his voice more tired than angry. \u8220\'93Especially not at night. I\u8217\'92m glad it was you and not\u8230\'85 I don\u8217\'92t know, a Chimaera or something.\u8221\'94 He ran a hand through his hair. \u8220\'93The rumors about Eddie\u8217\'92s attack are all over campus. No one feels safe walking alone after dark anymore.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Ashley\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s grin widened mischievously. She puffed out her chest and curled her hands into claws. \u8220\'93Maybe I }{\f0\fs24\i1 am}{ a Chimaera,\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94 she said, her voice a low growl. \u8220\'93A human-tiger hybrid, and I\u8217\'92m about to eat you! Waaaaargh!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {She clearly expected him to quip back, to shove her playfully or roll his eyes. But he didn\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92t. He just sighed and kept walking, his gaze fixed on the path ahead.}
\par\plain {The silence that followed was immediate. Ashley\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s playful demeanor vanished in an instant. She was happy-go-lucky, but she was also deeply empathetic, and his lack of response was a louder signal than any argument. She fell into step beside him, her expression turning serious and analytical.}
\par\plain {She let him walk for a few more paces before speaking, her voice gentle now.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re still worried about Eddie, aren\u8217\'92t you?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Will\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s shoulders sagged slightly. He tried to brush it off with a shrug, but he couldn\u8217\'92t meet her perceptive gaze. After a few more steps in silence, he sighed, the sound swallowed by the night air.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93I guess\u8230\'85 I was just feeling guilty about yesterday,\u8221\'94 he admitted, his voice low. \u8220\'93I shouldn't have been so harsh on him.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Ashley tilted her head, her curiosity genuine. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What makes you change your mind? You were okay with sneaking into the library and taking that book from the restricted section before. Why not now?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Because,\u8221\'94 Will said, stopping on the path and turning to face her fully. \u8220\'93I feel like this is something big. Bigger than us. I might not agree with how he\u8217\'92s been acting for the last few weeks, the secrecy and all that\u8230\'85 but I feel like he\u8217\'92s actually onto something this time.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93And that\u8217\'92s good, isn\u8217\'92t it?\u8221\'94 Ashley said, her voice becoming light and hopeful again. \u8220\'93If he\u8217\'92s right, then he can prove it and this whole thing will be over.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No,\u8221\'94 Will said, his expression grim. \u8220\'93It\u8217\'92s not good. Because if he\u8217\'92s right, he\u8217\'92s not up against the Student Council or the faculty anymore. If this is from the outside, then he's probably up against someone far more powerful.\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {The hope in Ashley\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s eyes flickered and died, replaced by a shared understanding of the danger. They started walking again, the silence between them heavier now. The only sounds were Will's steady footsteps on the stone and the occasional scuff of Ashley\u8217\'92s sneakers as she kicked a loose pebble along the path.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93He can\u8217\'92t do it alone,\u8221\'94 Will finally said, the words heavy with a conclusion he\u8217\'92d been fighting for days.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Then we shouldn\u8217\'92t let him be,\u8221\'94 Ashley replied instantly, her voice sure and clear.}
\par\plain {Will frowned in confusion. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What do you mean? We shouldn\u8217\'92t let him go?\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93No, dummy.\u8221\'94 Ashley nudged him hard with her elbow, a spark of her usual mischief returning. \u8220\'93We shouldn\u8217\'92t let him go }{\f0\fs24\i1 alone}{.\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {The simple clarification landed in Will\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s mind like a key turning in a lock. He stopped again, looking at her as the weight on his shoulders seemed to visibly lift. A slow smile spread across his face, a genuine one this time, reaching his eyes. He let out a short, relieved chuckle. She was right. It was that simple. They were a team.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93You\u8217\'92re insufferable,\u8221\'94 Will chuckled, shaking his head fondly as they started walking again, their steps now in sync.}
\par\plain {A genuine smile lit Will\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s face as they started walking again, the weight of his worry finally lifted. For the first time in weeks, it felt like they were back on the same page, a team again. The path ahead seemed a little brighter, the night air less oppressive.}
\par\plain {Their comfortable silence was shattered by a sharp, commanding shout that cut through the night.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Stop him!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Will and Ashley both froze, heads snapping in the direction of the voice. It came from the direction of the main quad, near the faculty buildings.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Is that\u8230\'85\u8221\'94 Ashley began, squinting into the distance.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Is that Eddie?\u8221\'94 Will finished, his own voice tight with a dawning sense of dread.}
\par\plain {As if on cue, a figure burst into view, sprinting past the gap between the Alchemy and Herbology halls. There was no mistaking the bellowing brown jacket and ripped jeans. It was Eddie. Seconds later, three more figures followed in hot pursuit: Victoria Aynesworth, her face a mask of cold fury, flanked by her two hulking Student Council guards.}
\par\plain {Will stared, his newfound peace evaporating into pure exasperation.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\i1 \loch\af1\hich\af1\dbch\af1\uc1\u8220\'93Bollocks,\u8221\'94}{ he cursed under his breath. \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93What did he do this time?!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {But before he could even fully process the scene, Ashley was already moving. With her  robes billowing behind her like a battle cloak in the wind, she broke into a dead sprint toward the chaos.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Come on!\u8221\'94 she shouted back at him, not even breaking stride. \u8220\'93We can still help him!\u8221\'94}
\par\plain {Will stood rooted to the spot for a single, agonizing moment. Every rational part of his brain screamed at him to turn around, to go back to the dorm, to stay out of it. This was it. This was the final warning. Getting involved now meant expulsion, no questions asked.}
\par\plain {He looked from Ashley\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s retreating figure to the chase unfolding across the quad. He saw his best friend, alone, running from a fight he couldn\u8217\'92t possibly win.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Screw it,\u8221\'94 he muttered to himself.}
\par\plain {He broke into a run, his satchel bouncing against his back as he sprinted to catch up.}
\par\plain {\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93Hey, Ash! Wait up!\u8221\'94}}